# Face mesh detection

This API is offered in beta, and is not subject to any SLA or deprecation policy. Changes may be made to this API that break backward compatibility.

![](https://developers.google.com/static/ml-kit/vision/face-mesh-detection/images/face_mesh_overview.png)

With ML Kit's face mesh detection API, you can generate in **real-time** a
**high accuracy mesh** of 468 3D points for selfie-like images. Faces should be
within \~2 meters (\~7 feet) of the camera.
> If you want to detect faces further than \~2 meters (\~7 feet) away from the
> camera, please see
> [ML Kit's face detection SDK](https://developers.google.com/ml-kit/vision/face-detection).

Here are some of the terms used regarding the face mesh detection feature:

- The **bounding box** is a rectangular area for a detected face.
- **Face mesh info** is a group of 468 3D points and edges that can be used to draw the geometry mesh for a detected face.

The face mesh detection API generates a [face mesh](https://developers.google.com/ml-kit/vision/face-mesh-detection/concepts)
for detected faces, each containing 468 3D points and edges. With face mesh
detection, you can perform more accurate operations on faces real-time, such as
AR filters, selfie capture, and video chat.

[Android](https://developers.google.com/ml-kit/vision/face-mesh-detection/android)

## Key capabilities

- **Recognize and locate faces** Get the bounding box for detected faces in a selfie-like picture.
- **Get face mesh information** Get the 468 3D points and triangle info for each detected face.
- **Process video frames in real time** Face mesh detection is performed on-device, and is fast enough for real-time applications, such as video manipulation.

